Subject: Re: [T2] How do the retractable belts work in an accident??

On Sun, 17 Nov 2002, Courtney Hook wrote:

> So I installed the 3 point retracting belts into my 70 bug so my daughter
> would be a little safer, but they don't seem to 'lock up' unless I really
> pull them out quickly and even then only about half the time.

Some belts work on the rate at which the belt is pulled out, others (like
stock VW/Audi self-adjusting belts) work with a pendulum inside the
retractor reel.

Yours sound fine.  They're really quite foolproof.

George
